**Contexto adicional:** If you supply the document fragments or at least their identifying metadata (title, document number, adoption date, publication reference in the Official Journal), I can identify which is most recent and cite the relevant dates/paragraphs. In general, to determine which EU instrument is most recent you should check the following elements in the provided material:
- the adoption or signature date shown on the document;
- the date of publication in the Official Journal (OJ L or OJ C) and the OJ reference;
- any stated entry into force date or amendment history (including corrigenda and successive amendments);
- whether a text is a consolidated version (which will indicate amendment dates).

Provide the documents or those metadata and I will compare dates and cite the exact provisions showing the relevant dates.
